{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01X9vG1zvCmRZtgsMGznjMc9","type":"tool_result","content":"<class 'dict'>\n{\n \"version\": 1,\n \"items\": [\n  {\n   \"category\": \"feature\",\n   \"description\": \"SLICE-0071: required summary field on all 5 template schemas, rendered atop the body, exposed as the --summary create flag\",\n   \"steps\": [\n    \"Add `summary: { type: string, required: true, min: 10, max: 200 }` to the schema block of all five templates/*.md (prd, slice, decision, doc, handoff)\",\n    \"Render a summary line at the top of each template body (under the id/title line)\",\n    \"Confirm createGeneric auto-derives the --summary flag and validation enforces min/max; omitting --summary fails with a missing-required-field error\",\n    \"Update existing test fixtures / create calls that now miss the required summary so the suite stays green\",\n    \"Add a test: create with --summary succeeds and renders the line; create without --summary fails; an existing artifact lacking summary still validates on read (grandfathered)\",\n    \"Verify: bun run build && bunx tsc --noEmit && bun test tests/\"\n   ],\n   \"passes\": true,\n   \"regression_notes\": \"\"\n  },\n  {\n   \"category\": \"feature\",\n   \"description\": \"SLICE-0072: generate a static per-project index.md at wiki sync (id, title, summary, status from frontmatter)\",\n   \"steps\": [\n    \"In src/cli/verbs/sync.ts, after the qmd embed loop, scan every artifact under projects/<project>/, read frontmatter (id, title, summary, status, group)\",\n    \"Write projects/<project>/index.md as plain markdown (table or list), sorted by kind then id, linked ids, no prose duplication, NO Dataview/Bases\",\n    \"Idempotent overwrite each sync; create must never write index.md\",\n    \"Add a test against a TEMP vault fixture (follow existing tests/ patterns): sync writes index.md listing the artifacts; re-running yields identical bytes\",\n    \"Verify: bun run bui