{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_018WtS1ueA9tKznM8Mqa1FYh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"advisor_tool_result","tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_016BzXGd1v23eGjNCs59Nsga","content":{"type":"advisor_result","text":"Approach is sound — sync-only generator, recursive walk, explicit sort, list-not-table to dodge pipe escaping. Go ahead. Before you write, nail these — they're what the test and the four ACs actually check, and your plan is silent on a couple:\n\n**Idempotency (the one AC that's directly tested — most likely to bite):**\n- Total order: sort by (kind, id). id is unique so that part's deterministic, but define an explicit *kind* order — iterate `ARTIFACTS` in wiki.json definition order (or alphabetical). Do **not** lean on `readdir` recursive order; it's not stable.\n- Exclude `index.md` and `_project.md` from the scan (you have this), and skip any file whose frontmatter has no recognizable id (`typeForId` → undefined) — that keeps stray/non-artifact files from perturbing output or throwing.\n- Fixed header, stable trailing newline, no counts/timestamps that drift.\n\n**Don't break the existing suite:**\n- Existing sync tests assert `stdout === \"\"`. Keep any \"wrote index\" logging on stderr or silent — never stdout. (Writing index.md into the temp fixtures won't touch the state-file/stdout assertions, so you're otherwise clear.)\n\n**Coverage the items.json step underspecifies but the slice ACs require:**\n- AC#4 \"create never touches index.md\" — add the cheap assertion (create an artifact, assert no index.md). You're only editing sync.ts so it holds, but the AC wants it proven, and it guards the guardrail.\n- Grandfathered vault artifacts lack `summary` — render undefined as empty, don't crash.\n\n**Placement:** inside the existing `try`, after the for-loop, before `return { code: 0 }`, called once with `project` (not per-target — research isn't a project dir). A qmd failure then correctly skips the index.\n\nNon-blocking note: after the first sync, the `**/*.md` mask will embed index.md itself on later runs. Not in scope to exclude — leave it, don't add mask logic.\n\nNone of this blocks the approach; it's the gap between green-first-try and chasing a flaky idempotency diff."}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4300,"cache_read_input_tokens":34465,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4300},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"28ab8cbe-87eb-42f8-8aa3-f40cdb29823c","uuid":"9f62b32a-4507-44e7-8a7d-cc6ee9d9d76f","request_id":"req_011CcLXCzS8UyJXCwtzkAWBM"}
